nib.text:
Your community needs your help to locate a missing dog. 

Ladybug, a Shar Pei, Pitbull, Retriever mix was inside of a 2008 gray Dodge Caliber that was stolen on Tuesday. 

The car is missing the front passenger hub cap and has front driver side bumper damage.

Ladybug has a scar on her rear left leg and wears a pink collar and a red therapy dog vest. 

She is a therapy dog whose owner is  U.S. Navy veteran.

If you've seen Ladybug or the vehicle she was in, leave a comment in the chat or Go Live.

nib.text:
A man was fatally shot inside a business in Cedar-Riverside on Tuesday evening, police said.

Officers responded to a report of a shooting on the 400 block of Cedar Avenue around 7 p.m.

When they arrived, police found a man with several gunshot wounds.

The victim was taken to a local hospital, where he died from his injuries.

Police did not release suspect information. 

Homicide investigators are working to determine what led to the shooting.
